SLS 26RS-4631 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 203
BY SENATOR BARROW
EMPLOYMENT. Creates the Louisiana Livable Wage Task Force.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To create the Louisiana Livable Wage Task Force to study the cost of living and make
3 recommendations to improve economic security for workers and families.
4 WHEREAS, Louisiana's current minimum wage is set at $7.25 per hour pursuant to
5 federal law; and
6 WHEREAS, working Louisianians are facing an increase in costs associated with
7 housing, health care, childcare, transportation, food, and other necessities; and
8 WHEREAS, ensuring that workers earn wages sufficient to meet basic living
9 expenses contributes to stronger families, healthier communities, reduced poverty, and
10 increased economic participation; and
11 WHEREAS, the current federal minimum wage of $7.25 per hour has remained
12 unchanged since July 24, 2009, and is insufficient for many working families in Louisiana
13 to meet basic living expenses; and
14 WHEREAS, the rising cost of housing, food, transportation, health care, and utilities
15 has increased financial hardship for workers across the state; and
16 WHEREAS, studies such as the Massachusetts Institute of Technology Living Wage
17 Calculator estimate that a true living wage in Louisiana would be substantially higher than
18 the current federal minimum wage; and
