1 WHEREAS, no person who works full time should be forced to live in poverty,
2 depend on charity, sleep in unsafe housing, or skip meals in order to survive; and
3 WHEREAS, economic justice is inseparable from human dignity and the moral
4 obligation of society to ensure that labor is compensated fairly and adequately; and
5 WHEREAS, the failure to establish a livable wage undermines families, weakens
6 communities, and contributes to preventable suffering across the state; and
7 WHEREAS, a comprehensive review of regional living costs and labor market
8 conditions is necessary to inform future policy decisions; and
9 WHEREAS, it is also necessary to study the economic conditions affecting workers
10 and employers in the community and to evaluate policy options that may support livable
11 wages while maintaining a healthy business climate.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
13 does hereby create the Louisiana Livable Wage Task Force, hereinafter referred to as the
14 "task force", to study and make recommendations concerning livable wages in Louisiana.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall do all of the following:
16 (1) Assess the cost of living in urban, suburban, and rural regions of Louisiana.
17 (2) Analyze the gap between current wages and cost of living.
18 (3) Study impacts on businesses, workers, and local economies.
19 (4) Solicit input from employees, employers, economists, community organizations,
20 and local governments.
21 (5) Recommend policies to improve economic security.
22 (6) Identify policies and practices that promote economic self-sufficiency and
23 workforce stability.
24 (7) Submit findings and recommendations for any legislation, administrative action,
25 memoranda of understanding, or other policy changes necessary to adopt a livable wage in
26 Louisiana.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall be composed of the
28 following members:
29 (1) The chairman of the Senate Committee on Labor and Industrial Relations.
30 (2) The member of the Senate representing Senate District 15.
