1 (3) The secretary of Louisiana Works, or her designee.
2 (4) The secretary of Louisiana Economic Development, or her designee.
3 (5) One member appointed by the Louisiana Association of Business and Industry
4 (LABI).
5 (6) One member appointed by the American Federation of Labor and Congress of
6 Industrial Organizations (AFL-CIO).
7 (7) One member appointed by the Greater Baton Rouge Economic Partnership.
8 (8) Two members who are low-wage worker representatives.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that each designating authority shall submit the name
10 of its appointee to the chairman of the Senate Committee on Labor and Industrial Relations
11 no later than August 1, 2026.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall convene its first meeting no
13 later than September 1, 2026, at the call of the chairman of the Senate Committee on Labor
14 and Industrial Relations and, at its first meeting, the members shall elect a chairman, vice
15 chairman, and any other officers the task force deems necessary. If the first meeting of the
16 task force is not convened by September 1, 2026, then the task force shall be deemed
17 terminated.
18 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Senate Committee on Labor and Industrial
19 Relations staff shall provide administrative support to the task force.
20 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the members of the task force shall
21 constitute a quorum for the transaction of business and that any official action of the task
22 force shall require the affirmative vote of a majority of the members present.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the task force shall serve
24 without compensation, except per diem or expenses reimbursement to which they may be
25 individually entitled as members of their constituent organizations.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall submit a written report of
27 its findings and recommendations no later than March 1, 2027, to Louisiana Works and the
28 Senate Committee on Labor and Industrial Relations, as required by R.S. 24:771 and 772.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall otherwise terminate on the
30 date of the submission of its report or March 1, 2027, whichever occurs first.
